# SSH Key for GitHub Deployment

## Public Key Generated
Copy this SSH key and add it to your GitHub account:

```
ssh-rsa  family-newsletter@deployment
```

## How to Add to GitHub

1. Go to GitHub.com → Settings → SSH and GPG keys
2. Click "New SSH key"
3. Title: "Family Newsletter Deployment"
4. Paste the key above
5. Save

## Once Added
I can then push the code using this SSH key.

Alternative: You can push manually using HTTPS with your Personal Access Token.
